f our polarised sources were found to be dominated by AGN\nactivity in the radio regime with most of them being radio-loud (79%) and of\nthe FRII class (87%). The host galaxies of our polarised source sample are\ndominated by intermediate disc and star-forming disc galaxies. The contribution\nof star formation to the radio emission is on the order of a few percent for\n$\\approx$10% of the polarised sources while for $\\approx$90% it is completely\ndominated by the AGN. We do not see any change in fractional polarisation for\ndifferent star-formation rates of the AGN host galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 31 Mar 2022 09:53:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-20"}
